headline: 3 Brilliant Growth Stocks That Can Outperform the S&P 500 by 2030
summary: The bull market has pushed the S&P 500 up 22% over the past year, but historically, the popular barometer has averaged about 10% returns annually.  To help you in your search, three Motley Fool contributors believe Uber Technologies (NYSE: UBER), MercadoLibre (NASDAQ: MELI), and Cava Group (NYSE: CAVA) have the makings of long-term winners that can outperform the broader market over the next five years.  John Ballard (Uber Technologies): Uber stock is up 162% since bottoming out in 2022, but the stock's flat performance over the past year sets up a great buying opportunity.
